# Rust / Cargo build artifacts
/target
**/target

# Cargo.lock is intentionally committed for the binary/workspace (reproducible
# CI builds). Remove the next line only if this becomes a published library.
# Cargo.lock

# Backtraces and profiling
*.profraw
perf.data*
flamegraph.svg

# Editor / OS noise
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json

# k2 toolchain output (reserved for future build artifacts)
/zig-cache/
/.k2-cache/
/k2-out/

# The examples' `build.lock` is regenerated output of `k2c build` (and the CLI
# tests), not a committed input. A real project commits its own `build.lock` for
# reproducible builds; here it is generated by running the toolchain.
/examples/build.lock
